About the author

AUTHOR: Arthur Boari

About the dashboard

This dashboard is a result of an assignment performed for PEX820 - Data Manipulation and Visualization. This course was enrolled in 2022/2 semester and belongs to the Graduate Program in Statistics and Agricultural Experimentation from Universidade Federal de Lavras (UFLA).

The data present in this dashboard comes from Spotify’s API (Spotify for Developers 2022) and was read into the R environment through the spotifyr (Thompson et al. 2021) package and manipulated using the tidyverse (Wickham et al. 2019) package. The Table presented on the next page showcases the data used from now on. We considered only the standard original recordings of all albums, although further analysis with the different editions and re-recordings are considered.

Other used packages: flexdashboard (Sievert et al. 2022), viridis (Garnier et al. 2021) and ggiraph (Gohel and Skintzos 2022).

Refer to the “References” page to view all sources of information and download the base and final dataset of this analysis.

Column

Taylor Swift Album Cover Coasters. First row: Midnights (2022), evermore (2020) and folklore (2020). Second row: Lover (2019), reputation (2017), 1989 (2014) and Red (2012 with 2021 re-record cover). Third row: Speak Now (2010), Fearless (2008 with 2021 re-record cover) and Taylor Swift (2006).
